cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper deals with security issues in the IPv6 Routing Protocol for Low-Power and Lossy Networks (RPL), which is a protocol used in the Internet of Things (IoT). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network infrastructure (routing) and system design (authentication), which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as likely categories. The paper also presents new attacks and extensions to mitigate them, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
